\begin_layout Standard
When reviewing the above plots we can see that the difference between the
 discrete and continous model increases when the intrest rate increases
 and when the discrete models compounding rate decreases.
 As such we can say that model 2 most accurately approximates model 1 when
 model 1 has a compounding rate that is large (in this case daily) and the
 intrest rate is relatively low.
 As such we can conclude that model 2 is an accurate approximation for the
 values showcased in this section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Quantitative Review
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
